  "body": "Geth version: 1.9.15-unstable\r\nOS & Version: Raspbian\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nTo start the eth node and begin syncing\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n```\r\ngeth[2599]: INFO [05-28|14:44:30.304] New local node record seq=650 id=d939bb35582980a4 ip= <MYIP> udp=30303 tcp=30303\r\ngeth[2599]: INFO [05-28|14:44:30.353] Mapped network port proto=tcp extport=30303 intport=30303 interface=\"UPNP IGDv1-IP1\"\r\ngeth[2599]: Fatal: Error starting protocol stack: listen unix /mnt/ethnode/ethereum/geth.ipc: bind: input/output error\r\nsystemd[1]: geth.service: Main process exited, code=exited, status=1/FAILURE \r\nsystemd[1]: geth.service: Failed with result 'exit-code'.\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n`geth --syncmode fast --cache 60 --datadir /mnt/ethnode/ethereum --port 30303`",
